	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p><addressee>Revr Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p>if it is possible for you to but the writings of <persName>Mrs<lb/> Levy</persName> is your Paper you would oblige much me<lb/> by so doing&#44; as I think also it would be probably<lb/> Interesting for your Paper&#44; or if you can&#39;t but<lb/> the whole in&#44; at least&#44; some <sic>coments</sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I remain you Respecfy</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">A Lowenstrit</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>Cleveland</placeName> <date>Novbr 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1887</date></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>With the Help of God.</p>
				<p><date><sic>tuesday</sic>&#44; October 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> the year <date>5612</date> according our calculation</p>
				<p>Peace &#38; happiness to my<lb/> friend the dear and respectable<lb/> man the great scholar<lb/> the pious man who is<lb/> known <del>all</del> over all the congregations<lb/> that are reassured all<lb/> over the <placeName>United States</placeName>.<lb/>  and famous for your notriety<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <persName>Rev. Isaack <sic>Lesser</sic></persName>.</p>
				<p>Being in distress I am<lb/> applying to you&#44; <del>my</del> your<lb/> honor or your name is<lb/> known to everyone as a<lb/> honest and <del>right</del> <sic>truthfull</sic><lb/> man.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">II</p>
				<p>I recd my copy which is<lb/> <sic>inclosed</sic> in this letter and<lb/> to criticize it thank to your<lb/> <del>long</del> great knowledge and to give<lb/> your opinion and trial<lb/> between me and my opponent<lb/> who is righteous<lb/> and how wise and <sic>plesant</sic> it<lb/> would be if your honor<lb/> will approve it grant me this copy<lb/> to be written <del>published</del> in original<lb/> Hebrew.  My journal will be<lb/> a monthly <del>one</del> edition and would<lb/> be called &#8220;Occident.&#8221;<lb/>  According my <sic>opinien</sic><lb/> it is a <add>Hebrew</add> to publish<lb/> and <sic>advertize</sic> among<lb/> all the Hebrew that live<lb/> in <placeName>U. S.</placeName></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">III</p>
				<p>and to save them from<lb/> low habits.</p>
				<p>You shall reward with<lb/> kindness find and<lb/> honest people and you shall<lb/> live long and succeed<lb/> in all your life&#39;s affairs<lb/> according my <sic>heartly</sic><lb/> wish your friend<lb/> who bends his head down<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <persName>Joseph</persName> the son of <persName>Isaac</persName><lb/> <del>who</del> <persName>Levy</persName>.  Who resides<lb/> in the Holy Community<lb/> the men of Mercy at<lb/> <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>.</p>
